  "instructions": [
    "Heat the coconut oil in the tagine over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and saut\u00176 until translucent.",
    "Add the ginger and garlic and saut\u00176 for another minute.",
    "Add the chettinad powder and saut\u00176 for 1 minute.",
    "Add the borlotti beans, chicken broth, tomato puree, salt, black pepper, and cayenne pepper. Stir well.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer for 30 minutes or until the borlotti beans are tender.",
    "Stir in the ghee and parmesan cheese.",
    "Garnish with fresh cilantro and serve.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy!",
    "This dish is best served with some crusty bread or over cauliflower rice for a low-carb option."
